 A quick video demonstrating the practical uses of some essential Linux commands. 

1️⃣ cat - Display file contents effortlessly. cat filename 
 Use Case: Quickly view the entire content of a file in one go.

2️⃣ echo - Print a line of text to the terminal. echo "Hello, World!" 
Use Case: Display messages or variables, great for scripting and debugging.

3️⃣ less - View file contents page by page. less filename 
Use Case: Easily navigate through large files without overwhelming your screen.

4️⃣ man - Access the manual for any command. man ls 
 Use Case: Get detailed information and options for commands directly from the terminal.

